For correct work u have to:

sudo apt install make cmake git

and clone this repo:
git clone https://github.com/opsengine/cpulimit.git

then do:
cd cpulimit
make 
sudo cp src/cpulimit /usr/bin

and now you can use this stuff.

troubleshooting:
if you've got a trouble with installing cmake on Astra 1.8 version, here are steps that could help you.

```
echo '# Основной репозиторий
deb https://dl.astralinux.ru/astra/frozen/1.8_x86-64/1.8.1/uu/2/main-repository/ 1.8_x86-64 contrib main non-free non-free-firmware
# Расширенный репозиторий
deb https://dl.astralinux.ru/astra/frozen/1.8_x86-64/1.8.1/uu/2/extended-repository/ 1.8_x86-64 contrib main non-free non-free-firmware' | sudo tee aboba.txt
```
and
`sudo apt update`
everyting should work fine.


